data.name: sqz
data.value: Utility that can manage compressed files.

data.name: CommonOptions.CompressionType
data.value: The compression type to use (gzip, deflate, or brotli)

data.name: sqz create
data.value: Creates a new compressed file from a source, optionally encrypting it with one of the supported .NET encryption algorithms.

data.name: CommonOptions.EncryptionAlg
data.value: The encryption algorithm to use when creating or uncompressing a file (none, AES, DES, TripleDES, RC2, Rijndael).

data.name: CommonOptions.Cipher
data.value: Cipher key/passphrase used to secure the encrypted file (required when --encryption is specified).

data.name: CommonOptions.LogLevel
data.value: The verbosity of the output logger ([m]inimal, [n]ormal, or [d]iagnostic).

data.name: OperationOptions.PrintSha
data.value: Display the SHA-256 hash code of the output file.

data.name: OperationOptions.Source
data.value: The source file used to create the compressed file.

data.name: OperationOptions.Output
data.value: Path and name of the output file to write.

data.name: sqz extract
data.value: Decrypts (if required) and decompresses a file.
